      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Championship Drama</h2>

      <p>World Championship finals produce the most memorable moments in competitive Scrabble. The pressure of a global title, combined with elite-level play, creates matches that the community discusses for decades.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 The 1991 Inaugural</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Peter Morris won the first-ever World Scrabble Championship in London, establishing America as an early competitive force. The event brought global legitimacy to competitive Scrabble and inspired decades of international competition.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🇫🇷 Richards Wins French (2015)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Nigel Richards won the French-language World Championship without speaking French — memorising 386,000 French words in 9 weeks. Universally considered the most extraordinary achievement in competitive word games history.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dramatic Comebacks and Upsets</h2>

      <p>The best Scrabble matches feature dramatic turning points — a single word that swings 100+ points, a perfectly-timed challenge, or an endgame calculation that steals victory from defeat.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why Upsets Happen in Scrabble</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Unlike chess, Scrabble has a <span class="text-white font-medium">significant luck component</span> from tile draws. Even the best player in the world loses 20-25% of their games. This means dramatic upsets are structurally built into the game — a lower-rated player can absolutely beat a champion on any given day with favorable tiles and solid play.</p>
      </div>

